a
ke - he couldna make the price of a sausage at it so - he had to - he had to go away from that - well he got a job as a - a lamplighter on the stairs, at that time - it was a very low wage, it wasnae very much, about seventeen shillings I think it was a w
e
ek at that time if I remember right, and it was a - pretty warm job for the likes of him, because - oh it's - climbing three storey you know that - morning and night you see, you lit them in the morning and - put them out at night. That was a - the only -
 the old days, but now they have a - these things is all changed now.
