 where the - where the Kelvin Hall is now, they used to call that the Bunhouse. That was what they called the Bunhouse at these days. It was a big - vacant big of ground that was given by a - a wealthy - man, he give the ground over to the people of 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Glasgow{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} you see. So we played football in that ground for - for years. And - just - and when you kicked the ball too hard it went over into 
