lankets was maybe in a tub you know, y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11668362\charrsid10055426 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12392121\charrsid10055426 
u'd tramp the blankets, get in there with 'em. 'Cos that was tramping the dirt out of the blankets in these days. See the - a wringer, a wee - like a - no like what you have nowadays. Had a wee wringer that you turn -
 turned with your own hands but - I used to hear my mother say, och I cann}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11668362\charrsid10055426 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
