Oh you - you had to - you had to make up orders like. Pack the butter and that, put as much water into it as you could. Things like that as I tell you and - make up orders like - sausages a
nd all these things you know. Put them in baskets and then the van take them away to the - to the customers, whoever it was. Oh that was quite a good job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9641210 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12392121\charrsid10055426 I suppose Coopers was quite a high class shop was it?
