\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid8660520 JL  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid12392121\charrsid10055426 Well - I don't know - of course a - a tradesman was definitely - he'd serv
ed - he'd served his time as an apprentice, well if you was a labourer you - you've been a labourer all your days so therefore you'd bigger money, you see. Well, now if you take an apprentice who served his time with maybe say seventeen shillings on his l
ast year - well the other - the other fellow has the edge that was labouring. He might have anything from - from a pound to thirty bob a week you see. Aye, there wasn't a - there were - were no any falling out about that, oh no. Oh no.
